    <h1>IoT Applications</h1>
    <hr>
    <h2>Activity 1 </h2>
    <hr>
    <h3>What is an IoT application? </h3>
    <p>It is a physical object that connects to the Internet. It can be a fitness tracker, a thermostat, a lock or appliance â€“ even a light bulb</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Used to analyse sensor data in cloud</li>
        <li>Machine learning algorithm is employed</li>
        <li>Embedded systems are connected to internet to collect and exchange data </li>
    </ul>
    <h3>What are the main Features needed?</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Artificial Intelligence</li>
        <li>connectivity</li>
        <li>data processing</li>
        <li>analyzing</li>
        <li>compactness of device</li>
        <li>Dynamic Nature</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>What are some Examples?</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Smartphone apps</li>
        <li>Biometric security system</li>
        <li>Industrial automation</li>
        <li>Smart watch</li>
        <li>IoT Retail Shops</li>
        <li>Smart Home</li>
    </ul>
    <hr>
    <h2>Activity 2</h2>
    <hr>
    <h3>What does smart mean?</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Refers to a system which does not require any user to operate.</li>
        <li>Requires sensors to sense data according to which it acts. </li>
        <li>Makes a system independent of any external source.</li>
        <li>Sense Think Act is an important paradigm employed in this</li>
        <li>Usually fault tolerant.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>What are the main Features needed?</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Eco Efficiency </li>
        <li>High Security</li>
        <li>Connecting building system</li>
        <li>Intelligent Sensor IOT</li>
        <li>Automated Processes</li>
        <li>Data Analytics</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>What are some Smart-building scenarios?</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Climate control including temperature, humidity, vibration etc.</li>
        <li>Air quality monitoring system</li>
        <li>Fire detection</li>
        <li>Lighting control system</li>
        <li>Earthquake detection</li>
        <li>Water level detection</li>
        <li>Structural health detection </li>
    </ul>
    <hr>
    <h2>Activity 3</h2>
    <hr>
    <h3>What are the high-level features?</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>AI assisted parking management</li>
        <li>Light directed Parking</li>
        <li>Automated temperature control </li>
        <li>Fire and Smoke detecting system</li>
        <li>Wireless charging for cars</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>What are the parts needed?</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Database to make a record of residents cars being parked</li>
        <li>Anti theft alarm</li>
        <li>Motion sensors and ultrasonic sensors </li>
        <li>Temperature sensor to make the parking temperature controlled.</li>
        <li>Electric car charging points</li>
        <li>High security camera system</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Who are the users?</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Residents of the building </li>
        <li>Guests</li>
        <li>Staff members of the building</li>
    </ul>

    
